<h2 id=3D"UpgradeOmniacorecontainerfrom2.0to2.1-1.Glossary">1. Glossary</h2=
>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
 <table class=3D"confluenceTable">
  <thead>
   <tr>
    <th class=3D"confluenceTh">Term</th>
    <th class=3D"confluenceTh">Meaning</th>
   </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
   <tr>
    <td class=3D"confluenceTd"><strong>OIM</strong></td>
    <td class=3D"confluenceTd">Omnia Infrastructure Manager host responsibl=
e for orchestrating Omnia services</td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
    <td class=3D"confluenceTd"><strong>Quadlet</strong></td>
    <td class=3D"confluenceTd">Systemd-native container unit file format fo=
r managing Podman containers</td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
    <td class=3D"confluenceTd"><strong>NFS</strong></td>
    <td class=3D"confluenceTd">Network File System - shared storage protoco=
l for persistent data</td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
    <td class=3D"confluenceTd"><strong>Rollback</strong></td>
    <td class=3D"confluenceTd">Process to revert to previous known-good sta=
te after upgrade failure</td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
    <td class=3D"confluenceTd"><strong>Migration</strong></td>
    <td class=3D"confluenceTd">Transformation of configuration files from 2=
.0 to 2.1 format</td>
   </tr>
  </tbody>
 </table>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"UpgradeOmniacorecontainerfrom2.0to2.1-2.Introduction">2. Introduc=
tion</h2>
<p>This High Level Design documents the upgrade of the Omnia core container=
 running within OIM from the current 1.0 image (running Omnia 2.0 code) to =
the 1.1 image carrying Omnia 2.1 code. The objective is to keep data intact=
, back up inputs and metadata, and guide operators through approval, upgrad=
e, and rollback.</p>
<h3 id=3D"UpgradeOmniacorecontainerfrom2.0to2.1-2.1Scope">2.1 Scope</h3>
<h4 id=3D"UpgradeOmniacorecontainerfrom2.0to2.1-InScope">In Scope</h4>
<ul>
 <li>Upgrading the Omnia core container image from 1.0 (Omnia 2.0 code) to =
1.1 (Omnia 2.1 code) within OIM.</li>
 <li>Producing a change/feature report for input/config migrations as part =
of the upgrade prompt.</li>
 <li>Creating backups of input files prior to any destructive action (other=
 configurations stay on the shared NFS volume and do not require backup).</=
li>
 <li>Executing the user-approved upgrade of Omnia Infrastructure Manager to=
 the 2.1 runtime.</li>
 <li>Applying migrations that produce input configs.</li>
 <li>Documenting rollback procedures leveraging the new backup artifacts.</=
li>
 <li>Communicating that any <strong>new feature enablement for the cluster =
requires a full re-provision</strong> on a fresh Omnia 2.1 deployment (no i=
n-place upgrades for feature adoption).</li>
 <li>Enabling the new <code>omnia.sh --upgrade</code> workflow which clones=
 Omnia 2.1 source, validates the current 1.0 container, prompts for a backu=
p destination (default <code>/</code>), and swaps in the 1.1 core container=
.</li>
</ul>
<h4 id=3D"UpgradeOmniacorecontainerfrom2.0to2.1-NotinScope">Not in Scope</h=
4>
<ul>
 <li>Adding new nodes to an upgraded cluster; such changes demand a fresh i=
nstall and full cluster re-provisioning on Omnia 2.1.</li>
 <li>Remediating versions earlier than Omnia 2.0.</li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"UpgradeOmniacorecontainerfrom2.0to2.1-2.2References">2.2 Referenc=
es</h3>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
 <table class=3D"confluenceTable">
